Innospec Performance Chemicals - Salisbury Plant RMP Executive Summary



The Innospec Performance Chemicals-Salisbury Plant has a long-standing commitment to worker and public safety and to the protection of the environment.  We are committed to operating and maintaining all of our processes in a safe and responsible manner, as demonstrated by the resources we invest to prevent accidents.  We are ISO 9001 and 14001 Certified meaning we have been audited by a 3rd party to ensure we have programs in place to not only comply with Safety and Environmental Standards, but that we have processes in place to ensure continual improvement in the areas of Safety,   Health, the Environment and Quality.  In addition to ensuring that our employees have the best training in the operation of our processes, we demand that safety be the first priority in the design, installation, operation and maintenance of our processes.

It is the policy of Innospec Performance Chemical's North Carolina Sites to develop, manufacture, and distribute materials with minimal impact on the environment and without injury to our employees, customers, and community.  To that end, Innospec Performance Chemicals North Carolina is committed to:

?    Protecting the Environment, Health, Safety, and Security of our employees, facilities and the community;

?    Operating our activities in compliance with applicable legal requirements and other requirements to which we subscribe relating to SHE aspects, as a minimum, while striving to achieve best industry practices;

?    Reducing the impact that our operations have on the environment through ongoing pollution prevention programs and energy and water use reduction programs;

?    Continuing improvement in Safety, Health, Environmental, and Security;

?    Communicating openly with our stakeholders;

?    Training all employees regarding the importance of Safety, Health, Environmental, and Security protection and the roles they play as stewards.



